GCR install it's own GLib log handler. This log handler writes all messages to
syslog. In GLib, the log handler is responsible for filtering messages by their
log level. However, GCR's log handler does not filter any messages. Therefore,
it also writes debug messages to the syslog which quickly pollutes the authlog.

The offending log handler has been removed in GCR-4.

See: https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/gcr/-/work_items/78

diff -upr gcr-3.41.2.orig/ui/gcr-prompter-tool.c gcr-3.41.2/ui/gcr-prompter-tool.c
--- gcr-3.41.2.orig/ui/gcr-prompter-tool.c	2026-06-13 14:12:00.465597685 +0200
+++ gcr-3.41.2/ui/gcr-prompter-tool.c	2026-06-13 14:12:34.159485229 +0200
@@ -154,8 +154,8 @@ log_handler (const gchar *log_domain,
 		level = LOG_INFO;
 		break;
 	case G_LOG_LEVEL_DEBUG:
-		level = LOG_DEBUG;
-		break;
+		// Do not log debug messages to syslog.
+		return;
 	default:
 		level = LOG_ERR;
 		break;
